,"text":"The offset of the view finder."}],"references":{"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration","title":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration","abstract":[{"text":"The view finder configuration object for a ‘SBSDKBaseScannerViewController’ and its subclasses.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Sometimes it is necessary to limit a live video frame detection or recognition to a certain rectangular area with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a specific aspect ratio: the region or rectangle of interest. This is where a view finder comes in.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It crops the video frame to that region of interest before passing it to any scanner. Usually","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the performance of scanners gain a benefit from it because less pixels must be processed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Additionally, to guide the user, the view finder visualizes the region of interest by drawing a rectangle around","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on the user interface.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SBSDKBaseScannerViewFinderConfiguration"}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkbasescannerviewfinderconfiguration","kind":"symbol"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Version: 8.0.1","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk","title":"ScanbotSDK","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","type":"topic"},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKBaseScann